articles.author: Mairead McArdle, Mairead McArdle
articles.title: Trump Signs $8.3 Billion Coronavirus Funding Bill
articles.description: President Trump on Friday signed an $8.3 billion emergency spending bill to combat the coronavirus as the number of cases of infected people in the U.S. passed 200 the day before.

articles.author: Mairead McArdle, Mairead McArdle
articles.title: University of Washington Becomes First U.S. College to Cancel Classes Due to Coronavirus
articles.description: The University of Washington in Seattle said Friday that it will move all classes online after a university staff member was diagnosed with the coronavirus this week.

articles.author: Mairead McArdle, Mairead McArdle
articles.title: U.S. Economy Adds 273,000 Jobs in February, Beating Expectations amid Coronavirus Scare
articles.description: The U.S. economy added 273,000 new jobs in February, almost 100,000 more positions than economists predicted.

articles.author: Zachary Evans, Zachary Evans
articles.title: Olympics Officials Discuss Holding Summer 2020 Games Without Spectators amid Coronavirus Fears
articles.description: Medical officers from various sports federations which run the Olympics have discussed with the World Health Organization the possibility of holding the 2020 summer Olympics without spectators.
